      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "TTS: enforce standalone directive lines parsing",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Problem: TTS directives were previously parsed with regex-heavy matching, which made standalone-line requirements implicit and easy to misinterpret (especially for text blocks and mixed line endings).\r\n- Why it matters: Ambiguous parsing can cause unexpected directive activation, inconsistent cleaned text behavior, and regression risk when input formatting varies (e.g., CRLF, extra blank lines, multiple text blocks).\r\n- What changed:\r\n  - Introduced internal line-by-line parsing helpers in `src/tts/directives.ts` with explicit states (`normal` / `in_tts_text_block`).\r\n  - Made standalone directive rules explicit in behavior:\r\n    - `[[tts:...]]` is recognized only when it occupies a full trimmed line.\r\n    - `[[tts:text]]` and `[[/tts:text]]` are recognized only when each appears on its own line.\r\n  - Preserved external API shape (`TtsDirectiveParseResult`) and compatibility of returned fields.\r\n  - Added regression coverage in `src/plugins/contracts/tts.contract.test.ts` for:\r\n    - CRLF (`\\r\\n`) directive parsing.\r\n    - Multiple consecutive `[[tts:text]]...[[/tts:text]]` blocks (first block wins).\r\n    - Stable blank-line preservation in `cleanedText`.\r\n  - Updated tagged-mode auto-TTS test input to use standalone block form so tests reflect intended directive semantics.\r\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary):\r\n  - No change to public parse result type shape.\r\n  - No change to provider override token semantics beyond standalone-line triggering requirements.\r\n  - No changes to unrelated TTS synthesis transport/provider runtime behavior.\r\n\r\n## Change Type (select all)\r\n\r\n- [x] Bug fix\r\n- [ ] Feature\r\n- [x] Refactor required for the fix\r\n- [ ] Docs\r\n- [ ] Security hardening\r\n- [ ] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n## Scope (select all touched areas)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\r\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n- [ ] Memory / storage\r\n- [ ] Integrations\r\n- [x] API / contracts\r\n- [ ] UI / DX\r\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n- Closes #<fill-if-applicable>\r\n- Related #<fill-if-applicable>\r\n- [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n## Root Cause / Regression History (if applicable)\r\n\r\n- Root cause: Directive recognition rules were embedded in broad regexes, so “standalone line only” behavior was implicit rather than explicit in parser control flow.\r\n- Missing detection / guardrail: Contract coverage did not lock in CRLF behavior, multi-block precedence, and blank-line stability around directive stripping.\r\n- Prior context (`git blame`, prior PR, issue, or refactor if known): Existing parser behavior relied on regex replacements for both directive lines and `tts:text` block extraction.\r\n- Why this regressed now: As directive usage expanded, edge cases became more visible (line ending variations and block formatting differences).\r\n- If unknown, what was ruled out: N/A.\r\n\r\n## Regression Test Plan (if applicable)\r\n\r\n- Coverage level that should have caught this:\r\n  - [x] Unit test\r\n  - [x] Seam / integration test\r\n  - [ ] End-to-end test\r\n  - [ ] Existing coverage already sufficient\r\n- Target test or file: `src/plugins/contracts/tts.contract.test.ts`\r\n- Scenario the test should lock in:\r\n  - Standalone directive parsing with CRLF.\r\n  - First-block-wins behavior for multiple `tts:text` blocks.\r\n  - Stable whitespace retention in `cleanedText` after directive removal.\r\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: The contract suite exercises parser behavior through the same exported seams used by runtime TTS flow.\r\n- Existing test that already covers this (if any): Existing parse directive tests cover baseline extraction and inline literal non-trigger behavior.\r\n- If no new test is added, why not: N/A (new tests were added).\r\n\r\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\r\n\r\n- Inline literal directive strings (embedded inside normal sentence text) remain non-triggering.\r\n- Directive activation is now strictly tied to standalone lines for `[[tts:...]]` and `[[tts:text]]` block markers.\r\n- Behavior is consistent across LF and CRLF inputs.\r\n\r\n## Diagram (if applicable)\r\n\r\n```text\r\nBefore:\r\n[text with directive-like patterns]\r\n  -> regex replace paths\r\n  -> directive activation could be harder to reason about from control flow\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n[text]\r\n  -> line scanner (normal / in_tts_text_block)\r\n  -> standalone line checks\r\n  -> structured parse result\r\n  -> deterministic cleanedText + overrides",
        "branch": "jimmy/2026-03-29-01-48-34",
